properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued February 8 at 2:34PM CST until February 9 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...SNOW EXPECTED ON SUNDAY...

.A low pressure system will track from the central Plains toward
southern Wisconsin on Sunday and into Lower Michigan Sunday
evening. Snow will spread across the area from southwest to
northeast during the morning, continue through afternoon, and then
end during the evening.

* WHAT...Heavy snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 7 to 9
inches.

* WHERE...Wood, Portage, Waupaca and Waushara Counties.

* WHEN...From 6 AM to 6 PM CST Sunday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could become hazardous.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The heaviest snow is expected to fall from
late morning into early afternoon. Expect snow-covered and
slippery road conditions, along with greatly reduced visibility.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 6 AM TO 6 PM CST SUNDAY
